                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <seg type="script">Written in a fine handwriting, sometimes uneven.</seg>
                                <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                                <seg type="rubrication">Introductory expressions of direct speech in <ref target="#i5"/>, such as: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኀበ፡ ተናገረ፡, 
                                    ወደገመ፡ ነገረ፡, ወዓዲ፡ ነገረ፡</foreign>, etc.</seg>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <desc type="Record"/>
                                    <locus target="#1r"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">History of our Fathers, the monks who sprang from Dabra Libānos: ʾAnorewos of Warab, Tadewos of Ṭǝlālǝš and Dabra 
                                        Dǝḫuḫān, Gabra Krǝstos of Dǝmbiyā, Zenā Mārqos of Morat, Sāmuʾel of Dabra Wagal (sic), Yosef of ʾƎnnārʾǝt, Qawestos of M(aḥ)āggǝl, 
                                        ʾAdḫānani (sic) of Dāmot, ʾIyosyās of Waǧ, Matyas of Faṭagār, another ʾAdḫānani (sic) of Dawāro, Madḫane ʾƎgziʾ of Tǝgrāy. All of them 
                                        fulfill their office, each according to their own rank".</q>
                                    <note>The note records the names of prominent personalities coming from the monastic community of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2297DabraL">Dabra Libānos</placeName>:
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1955Anorewos">ʾAnorewos</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9087Tadewos">Tādewos</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4279GabraKr">Gabra Krǝstos</persName>, 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10708ZenaMa">Zenā Mārqos</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8485Samuel">Sāmuʾel</persName>, <persName cert="low" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10455Yosef">Yosef</persName>, 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8023Qawestos">Qawǝsṭos</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1417Adhani">ʾAdḫāni</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10778Iyosyas">ʾIyosyās of Wag</persName>, 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6913Matyas">Matyas</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10779Adhani">Adḫāni of Dawāro</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6445Madhanin">Madḫānina ʾƎgziʾ</persName>.
                                        The note displays resemblance with a passage of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1445GadlaF">Gadla Filǝṗṗos za-Dabra Libānos</ref> and of the 
                                        <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3143Ledata">Lǝdata ʾabaw</ref>.
                                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/X2JEJBEJ"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Turaiev1908Aaron"/><title level="m">Vitae Sanctorum Indigenarum. II. Acta S. Aaronis et Philippi</title><title level="s">Corpus Scriptorum Christianorum Orientalium</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Boris</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Turaiev</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Parisiis</pubPlace><publisher>E typographeo reipublicae</publisher><date>1908</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Corpus Scriptorum Christianorum Orientalium</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">Scriptores Aethiopici, II, 20</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">Scriptores Aethiopici, II, 20</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">198 (text), 179 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>
                                        <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/CB9GUS9K"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Getachew1983monastic"/><title level="a">The Monastic Genealogy of the Line of Täklä Haymanot of Shoa</title><title level="j">Rassegna di Studi Etiopici</title><author><name>Getatchew Haile</name></author><date>1982_1983</date><biblScope unit="volume">29</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">7-38</biblScope><note type="url">http://www.jstor.org/stable/41299670</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Täklä Haymanot</note><note type="tag">bm:Getachew1983monastic</note><note type="tag">bm:Getatchew1982Monast</note></note><note type="tag">Täklä Haymanot</note><note type="tag">bm:Getachew1983monastic</note><note type="tag">bm:Getatchew1982Monast</note><citedRange unit="page">28-29</citedRange></bibl>
                                    </note>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <locus target="#35r"/>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">ቃሉ፡ ፻ወ፷፫፻፴ወ፱ ጥበበ፡ ሰሎሞን።</q>
                                    <q xml:lang="en">"Words: 16,339, Wisdom of Solomon".</q>
                                    <note>Stichometry of <ref target="#i4"/>.</note>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <locus target="#76"/>
                                    <note>Interpretation of foreign words, such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Κυριε ἐλεισον, ἁγια</foreign>, and others.</note>
                                </item>
                                <item xml:id="e3">
                                    <note>Glosses and corrections are written on the margin of many leaves.</note>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
